Third-party attributions
-----------------------

ExtensionShield incorporates or was inspired by the following:

- ThreatXtension (https://github.com/barvhaim/ThreatXtension)
  ThreatXtension is distributed under the MIT License (declared in its upstream
  README; no separate LICENSE file is published in the upstream repository, so
  the exact upstream copyright text is not reproduced here).

  We took inspiration from ThreatXtension in the same space (Chrome extension
  security scanning, VirusTotal integration). The initial security score
  aggregation logic (risk points by category) was inspired by ThreatXtension;
  ExtensionShield's primary scoring is the V2 ScoringEngine (multi-layer,
  gates, governance) in extension_shield.scoring.engine.

  A set of Semgrep malware-detection rules in
  src/extension_shield/config/custom_semgrep_rules.yaml (credential theft,
  cookie theft, C2/exfiltration, keylogger, clipboard, URL hijacking, and
  tracking) was adapted from ThreatXtension's MIT-licensed Semgrep ruleset;
  see the in-file section header for the local attribution.

  Supabase migration schemas were initially derived from SQLite schema
  patterns from that project; see supabase/migrations/ and supabase/schemas/
  for file-level comments.

